#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn35.71"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.71:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.71:0.2"
msgid "7. Migajālavagga "
msgstr "7. With Migajāla "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 71. Paṭhamachaphassāyatanasutta → chaphassāyatanikā 1 (pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.71:0.3"
msgid "71. Paṭhamachaphassāyatanasutta "
msgstr "71. Six Fields of Contact (1st) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn35.71:1.1"
msgid "“Yo hi koci, bhikkhave, bhikkhu channaṃ phassāyatanānaṃ samudayañca atthaṅgamañca assādañca ādīnavañca nissaraṇañca yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, anyone who doesn’t truly understand the six fields of contacts’ origin, ending, gratification, drawback, and escape "

msgctxt "sn35.71:1.2"
msgid "Avusitaṃ tena brahmacariyaṃ, ārakā so imasmā dhammavinayā”ti. "
msgstr "has not completed the spiritual journey and is far from this teaching and training.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn35.71:2.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, aññataro bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When he said this, one of the mendicants said to the Buddha, "

#. VAR: anassasaṃ → anassāsiṃ (bj, pts1) | anassāsaṃ (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn35.71:2.2"
msgid "“etthāhaṃ, bhante, anassasaṃ. "
msgstr "“Here, sir, I’m lost. "

msgctxt "sn35.71:2.3"
msgid "Ahañhi, bhante, channaṃ phassāyatanānaṃ samudayañca atthaṅgamañca assādañca ādīnavañca nissaraṇañca yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāmī”ti. "
msgstr "For I don’t truly understand the six fields of contacts’ origin, ending, gratification, drawback, and escape.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn35.71:3.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, bhikkhu, "
msgstr "“What do you think, mendicant? "

msgctxt "sn35.71:3.2"
msgid "cakkhuṃ ‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’ti samanupassasī”ti? "
msgstr "Do you regard the eye like this: ‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn35.71:4.1"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“No, sir.” "

# NOTE: BB has “you should …” but the text has bhavissati. This is unusual in such a context, and I think it is a specific encouragement for the depressed monk. This would be an example of the Buddha’s knowledge of “where all paths lead”.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn35.71:5.1"
msgid "“Sādhu, bhikkhu, ettha ca te, bhikkhu, cakkhu ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya sudiṭṭhaṃ bhavissati. "
msgstr "“Good, mendicant! And regarding the eye, you will truly see clearly with right wisdom that: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’ "

msgctxt "sn35.71:5.2"
msgid "Esevanto dukkhassa … pe … "
msgstr "Just this is the end of suffering. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.71:5.3"
msgid "jivhaṃ ‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’ti samanupassasī”ti? "
msgstr "Do you regard the ear … nose … tongue … body … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn35.71:6.1"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn35.71:7.1"
msgid "“Sādhu, bhikkhu, ettha ca te, bhikkhu, jivhā ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya sudiṭṭhaṃ bhavissati. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn35.71:7.2"
msgid "Esevanto dukkhassa … pe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn35.71:7.3"
msgid "manaṃ ‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’ti samanupassasī”ti? "
msgstr "Do you regard the mind like this: ‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "sn35.71:8.1"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“No, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "sn35.71:9.1"
msgid "“Sādhu, bhikkhu, ettha ca te, bhikkhu, mano ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya sudiṭṭhaṃ bhavissati. "
msgstr "“Good, mendicant! And regarding the mind, you will truly see clearly with right wisdom that: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’ "

msgctxt "sn35.71:9.2"
msgid "Esevanto dukkhassā”ti. "
msgstr "Just this is the end of suffering.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.71:9.3"
msgid "Navamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

